    "description": {
      "en": {
        "provenance": "imported",
        "value": "Personnel Services : FAO will provide the project with technical Services of Technical Cooperation among Developing Countries (TCDC) and National Consultants as following:\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nTCDC experts (2. 0 P/M) on\r\n\r\n\r\n\tSustainable Management and Development of NWFP expert- 60 days (three missions: 20+20+20 days)\r\n\r\n\r\n                 \r\n\r\nNational consultants (26 p/m):\r\n\r\n\r\n\tCultivation and Production Specialist cum Team Leader- 12 months\r\n\tConservation and Extension Specialist- 6 months\r\n\tProcessing and Value addition Specialist- 6 months\r\n\tPolicy expert- 2 months\r\n\r\n\r\nTechnical support services (Total 40/days)\r\n\r\nRAPO and FOEP will undertake four missions (40 days) in support of the project.\r\n\r\n\r\n\tRAPO officer ( LTO)- 30 days\r\n\r\n\r\n      30 days (8+7+7) for three specific missions and 8 days for standard\r\n\r\n\r\n\tForestry Officer (Microenterprises) from FOEP- 10 days\r\n\r\n\r\n       10 days: 7 days for specific mission and 3 days for standard\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nContract : preparation of Video film and interactive CDs for training.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nMaterials, supplies and equipment \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nTraining and workshop:  The project will include mainly three types of workshops such as inception, stakeholder consultations (policy, processing and value addition, training material preparation and validation, etc), and terminal. Altogether, there will be more than 120 participants (about 40 of each workshop)."
      },
